This function acts as a getter that wraps the offset calculation in a watcher pattern. It checks if the underlying offset accessor is callable to determine how parameters are tracked and monitored when initializing the observer.

```python
def offset(self):
        """
        Property to be used for setting and getting the offset of the layer.

        Note that setting this property causes an immediate redraw.
        """
        if callable(self._offset):
            return util.WatchingList(self._offset(*(self.widget.pos+self.widget.size)),self._wlredraw_offset)
        else:
            return util.WatchingList(self._offset,self._wlredraw_offset)
```

Remember that because this property returns a `util.WatchingList`, retrieving it immediately sets up logic to redraw the view whenever the offset changes.
